  ESLint, which the agent meticulously resolved by updating configurations and
  migrating to the new flat config format for ESLint. The agent also refactored
  the auth system to use Web Crypto API for Edge Runtime compatibility and
  implemented lazy-loading for the Prisma client to prevent build-time
  connection errors. Finally, e2e tests were updated to reflect the current
  application content. After resolving all these issues, all GitHub Actions and
  Vercel deployments passed, and the PR was deemed ready for merge. The
  conversation concluded with the user reporting a new bug regarding an
  incorrect progress indicator on the first step.
